Welshman Nigel Owens will referee Saturday's Test between France and South Africa in Paris. Owens will be assisted by three Englishmen - Wayne Barnes and Tom Foley as assistant referees - and Rowan Kitt as television match official (TMO). Saturday's Test at the Stade de France is scheduled for 21:45 (SA time). The Springboks' last two Tests on tour will be refereed by two Frenchmen, Romain Poite (v Italy, November 25) and Jerome Garces (v Wales, December 2). Source: Sport24